def convert1d2d(arr):
    # convert (m, ) to (m, 1), i.e. 1d to 2d 
    return np.reshape(arr, (-1, 1))

# plotting, green = default, blue = scaled, red = normalized 
fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(20, 20))
for ax in axs.flat:
    ax.grid(True)

axs[0][0].hist(tension, bins=[i for i in range(0,101,5)], facecolor='g', alpha=0.5, rwidth=0.95, range=[0,tension.max()])
axs[0][1].hist(tension, 100, facecolor='g', alpha=0.5,rwidth=0.95, range=[0,100])
axs[1][0].hist(tension_scaled, bins=[i/100 for i in range(0,101,5)], facecolor='b', alpha=0.5, rwidth=0.95)
axs[1][1].hist(tension_scaled, 100, facecolor='b', alpha=0.5, rwidth=0.95)
axs[2][0].hist(tension_norm, bins=[i for i in range(0,101,5)], facecolor='r', alpha=0.5, rwidth=0.95, range=[0,tension_norm.max()])
axs[2][1].hist(tension_norm, 100, facecolor='r', alpha=0.5, rwidth=0.95, range=[0,100])

plt.show()
